<doc id="2308" url="https://ne.wikipedia.org/wiki?curid=2308" title="हृदयशास्त्र">
हृदयशास्त्र

Cardiology is the branch of medicine dealing with disorders of the heart and blood vessels. The field is commonly divided in the branches of "congenital heart defects", "coronary artery disease", "heart failure", "valvular heart disease" and "electrophysiology". Physicians specializing in this field of medicine are called cardiologists.

The term "cardiology" is derived from the Greek word "καρδιά" (transliterated as "kardia" and meaning "heart" or "inner self").

















The followings are medications commonly prescribed in cardiology:



Cardiology is the branch of medicine dealing with disorders of the heart र blood vessels. The field is commonly divided in the branches of "congenital heart defects", "coronary artery disease", "heart failure", "valvular heart disease" र "electrophysiology". Physicians specializing in this field of medicine are called cardiologists.

The term "cardiology" is derived from the Greek word "καρδιά" (transliterated as "kardia" र meaning "heart" or "inner self").

















The followings are medications commonly prescribed in cardiology:



